feat(m2-text-channels): create text channels and send/receive live persisted messages

Suggested PR body:
Delivers the M2 acceptance loop (SPEC.md §14): any member can create a text channel via
POST /api/channels, send/receive plain-text messages live across all connected clients over
the WS gateway (message.send -> persisted -> message.create broadcast), and on reload/relaunch
see the persisted channel list (ready.channels) and message history (GET /api/channels/:id/messages
with keyset pagination). Flat membership, ≤10 clients, plain text only; images (M3) and voice (M4)
remain out of scope.

